<section class="brand--department-for-business-innovation-skills brand__border-color organisation__brand-border-top organisation__section-wrap organisation__margin-bottom" id="what-we-do">
  <div class="grid-row">
    <div class="column-two-thirds">
      <h2 class="gem-c-heading  gem-c-heading--padding gem-c-heading--margin-bottom-2  ">What the Industrial Development Advisory Board does</h2>

    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid-row">
    <div class="column-two-thirds">
      
<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak " data-module="govspeak">
    
          <p></p>
<div class="govspeak">
<p>The Industrial Development Advisory Board (IDAB) advises ministers on applications from companies proposing to start capital investment projects in the Assisted Areas in England and who have applied for regional selective assistance under the Grant for Business Investment scheme or the Regional Growth Fund.</p>

<p><abbr title="Industrial Development Advisory Board">IDAB</abbr> is an advisory non-departmental public body, sponsored by the <a class="brand__color" href="/government/organisations/department-for-business-energy-and-industrial-strategy">Department for Business, Energy & Industrial Strategy</a>.</p>
</div>

          <p>
            <a href="/government/organisations/industrial-development-advisory-board/about" class="brand__color">
              Read more about what we do
            </a>
          </p>

</div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>



